subjective.chief_complaint: Headache on left side a few hours ago
subjective.hpi: Patient presents with a gradual, throbbing headache on the left side starting a few hours ago with no radiation. Reports visual aura consisting of zigzag lines before onset. Associated symptoms include photophobia, blurred vision, nausea, and two episodes of vomiting today. Also reports neck pain but no stiffness. Denies speech disturbance, limb weakness, or numbness. No recent head injury, fever, or rashes. Reports a similar episode 2 weeks ago which resolved with analgesics. Patient expresses significant worry about brain cancer. Lives alone, works in fashion industry with high stress levels. Denies mood symptoms, smoking, or alcohol use.
subjective.patient_history: Past Medical History: None (Nil). Drug History: Microgynon (COCP). Family History: Mother with migraine. Social History: High stress, lives alone, no smoking/etOH.

physical_exam.text_raw: Neuro checks: No speech disturbance, no limb weakness/numbness. Neck: Pain present, no stiffness.

procedures_ordered: Change Combined Oral Contraceptive Pill (COCP) to Progestogen-Only Pill (POP)
Review in 1 week to discuss prophylactic treatment
plan.patient_instructions: Review earlier if symptoms worsen (increased headache, vomiting, vision changes) or if concerns arise.
